        <heading>Connecticut Partnership for Long-Term Care</heading>
        <section eId="sec_17b_126">
          <num>17b-126</num>
          <heading>(Formerly Sec. 17-281). Lien against real property</heading>
          <content>
            <p>Sec. 17b-126. (Formerly Sec. 17-281). Lien against real property.If any person receiving such aid neglects or refuses to sign such agreement, the selectmen are authorized to file a lien against such property, or against the real property of any legally liable relative of any person receiving aid or support under sections17b-194,17b-222to17b-250, inclusive,17b-263,17b-340to17b-350, inclusive,17b-689band17b-743to17b-747, inclusive, to secure the disbursements of such town made prior to filing such lien and any disbursements thereafter made, and such lien from the time of filing shall have the same force and effect and may be foreclosed in the same manner as any agreement provided for in section17b-125.
